trait_info: The stage 1 phyllosoma time series was significantly correlated with several time series related to ocean temperature: the sea-surface temperature (SST) time series averaged from the CalCOFI surveys (r = 0.39, p < 0.01), the MEI (r = 0.30, p < 0.05), and the PDO (r = 0.35, p < 0.05) (fig. 8).All correlations indicate that relatively warm ocean conditions, including El Niño events and the warm phase of the PDO, are positively associated the abundance of phyllosoma.
